SIMPLE: floater
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Floater
<hw>Float"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who
floats or swims.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A float for indicating the height of a liquid
surface.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Politics)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A voter who
shifts from party to party, esp. one whose vote is purchasable.</def>
<mark>[U. S.]</mark> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A person, as a delegate to a
convention or a member of a legislature, who represents an irregular
constituency, as one formed by a union of the voters of two counties
neither of which has a number sufficient to be allowed a (or an extra)
representative of its own.</def> <mark>[U. S.]</mark> <sd>(c)</sd>
<def>A person who votes illegally in various polling places or election
districts, either under false registration made by himself or under the
name of some properly registered person who has not already voted.</def>
<mark>[U. S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Floating</ent>⟦br⟧
